Goal:
The purpose is to test the machine trap delegation and improve coverage in intpipe_csr_file. More details in VERIF-1886.

Parameter(s):
Core - This test will run on any Core (even thread) of any Neighborhood of any Shire. Only 1 Core (even thread) is expected to be enabled.

Details:
A microkernel test that starts in M-mode:
Contains two exception handlers: "M" and "S", both logging that they have been hit (by increasing a counter) and returning the priviledge level in which they are running. The "M" handler also sets medeleg for the "user ecall" exception to be delegated to S-mode.
Sets mtvec for handling a "user ecall" with handler "M".
Sets stvec for handling a "user ecall" with handler "S".
Switches to U-mode.
Issues a "user ecall", verifying that the "M" handler was hit and its priviledge level was M-mode. This M-mode handler will have set medeleg for any subsequent ecall to be delegated.
Issues another "user ecall", verifying that this second time the handler "S" was hit and its privilege level was S-mode.
